Financial Analyst --Alex - Int'l Co.
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/03 18:10:48
Ref. JB3046830
Job Description
Job Purpose:
To provide analysis of and commentaries on the Company financial data, assist with the preparation of budgets and quarterly forecasts, project reviews.
Primary Objectives of the Role:
Analysis of monthly financial data
Consolidation of budget data, commentary & completion of Company and Group reporting requirements
Consolidation of quarterly forecasts, commentary & completion of Company and Group reporting requirements
Financial modelling and assessment of projects (capex and operational)
Checking and controlling costs versus budget
Internal audit of Company’s controls and procedures
Support to Marketing dept in all financial evaluations
Description of Duties
Decision Making
To provide recommendations on project analysis
Communications
•Routine communication with CFO, Senior Finance Manager and finance staff.
•Presentations to senior staff
•Requirements to communicate across the business
Skills
Experience & Knowledge
•Min. 5 Years Experience in relevant Field
•Reporting Skills
•Analysing Information
•ORACLE financials
•Microsoft Office (Excel/Word/PowerPoint)
Qualifications
Qualified Accountant
